## Installing powershell in Linux Mint

# Updated package list and installed prerequisites
sudo apt update && sudo apt install -y wget apt-transport-https software-properties-common

# Downloaded the Microsoft repository GPG keys
wget -q https://packages.microsoft.com/config/ubuntu/24.04/packages-microsoft-prod.deb

# Registered the Microsoft repos GPG keys
sudo dpkg -i packages-microsoft-prod.deb

# Update the list of packages after adding the repo
sudo apt update

# Install PowerShell
sudo apt install -y powershell

# To start PowerShell in the terminal
pwsh
